\title{Type Family}
\taxon{Definition}
\import{macros}
\p{
    Consider a type #{A} in context #{\Gamma}.
    A \strong{family} of types over #{A} in context #{\Gamma}
    is a type #{B(x)} in context #{\Gamma, x:A}.
    ##{
        \Gamma, x:A \vdash B(x) \type
    }
    #{B} is a family of types over #{A} in context #{\Gamma}.
    Alternatively, we say that #{B(x)} is a type \strong{indexed} by #{x:A} in context #{\Gamma}.
}